  <h3><a name="borenstein">Greg Borenstein</a></h3>
  <p>Greg Borenstein is a programmer and musician in Portland, Oregon. He is the author of a number of open source projects including <a href="http://rad.rubyforge.org">RAD</a>, a library for programming the Arduino open source hardware platform in Ruby. In his spare time, Greg organizes PDX Pop Now!, a free all-ages local music festival and non-profit organization, and blogs about Ruby, art, and hardware hacking on <a href="http://urbanhonking.com/ideasfordozens">Urban Honking</a>. Ruby was the first programming language he ever learned.</p>
